# What is libupdate?

This package is a tool to check for updates of installed Python libraries 
and suggest for upgrades.


# How to install?

You can install the package using:

pip install pylibupdator

![](src/Image2.png)

# Usage

In command prompt, run below code:

pylibupdate


![](src/Image1.png)

![](src/Image3.png)


# Look Here:

Check your desktop for "Libraries To Upgrade.txt" file. Open the .txt file in any editor to view/upgrade 
the existing libraries.


![](src/Image4.png)


